	quest.01F396184B1D8764.quest_subtitle: "Smelt the sand-iron into living steel"
	quest.01F396184B1D8764.quest_desc: [
		"Tamahagane is born in the tatara furnace from black satetsu sand."
		"Forge four tamahagane ingots, the pure steel that becomes the blade."
		"This is the heart of the swordsmith's art."
	]
	quest.037ECAB1A15D401E.quest_subtitle: "Flood the paddy and set the seedlings in straight rows"
	quest.037ECAB1A15D401E.quest_desc: [
		"Spring rains fill the paddy, and the work of the year begins."
		"Wade into the mud and press the young rice into the flooded earth, row by patient row."
		"Plant the rice (ine) and the village will not go hungry come winter."
		"Take up the rake and the seedling. The first calling of the noka is the soil itself."
	]
	quest.06E7CDA90DD62A0B.quest_subtitle: "Earn the right to call yourself meiko"
	quest.06E7CDA90DD62A0B.quest_desc: [
		"The master craftsman, the meiko, works metals lesser hands cannot."
		"Smith a hihi'irokane ingot, the netherite of the southern mines."
		"Master both steel and the dark ore, and the masters will know your name."
	]
	quest.0983A81ECE90EBBC.quest_subtitle: "The mind that does not waver"
	quest.0983A81ECE90EBBC.quest_desc: [
		"Fudōshin, the immovable mind. When the line wavers, the footsoldier does not. Fear passes through him and finds no place to rest."
		"Hold the ground others abandon. Cut down the foe though the earth shakes."
		"Steel for the legs of one who never takes a backward step."
	]
	quest.0A6355B7E8808750.quest_subtitle: "Set the hammer to fall on its own"
	quest.0A6355B7E8808750.quest_desc: [
		"The shikake, the hidden contrivance, does the work of many hands."
		"Assemble a mechanical press to stamp sheets and plates without tiring,"
		"and let the machine repeat what once cost you sweat."
	]
	quest.0BBE4A9EEC507EAE.quest_subtitle: "Joinery without a single nail"
	quest.0BBE4A9EEC507EAE.quest_desc: [
		"The old masters raised halls that have stood a thousand years, and not one was held by iron."
		"Cut and fit stairs of spirit-blossom wood. Where the grain meets the grain, there the strength lives."
		"Reward: spirit-blossom wood for the joints to come."
	]
	quest.0D984FBA2C5EE04C.quest_subtitle: "Light through washi paper"
	quest.0D984FBA2C5EE04C.quest_desc: [
		"The shoji screen divides a room without closing it, and turns harsh sun into soft morning light."
		"Fashion shoji panels of sakura. A wall that breathes is the mark of a careful hand."
		"Reward: shoji frames and paper lanterns to dress the hall."
	]
	quest.0E24432AB0D51D1D.quest_subtitle: "Goma, the fire offering"
	quest.0E24432AB0D51D1D.quest_desc: [
		"Mark the ground with sacred chalk and raise the goma fire. Into its flame the ascetic casts his desires and his fears, that they burn to nothing."
		"Gather white ritual chalk and lay the boundary of the rite."
		"Take the golden bowl, that your offerings may be received."
	]
	quest.0F9B983A73EE1C19.quest_subtitle: "The crowning of the pagoda"
	quest.0F9B983A73EE1C19.quest_desc: [
		"Master your full craft and the pagoda rises tier upon tier, each roof lighter than the last."
		"The miyadaiku who reaches this rank carries the temple in his hands and the village in his name."
		"Reward: pagoda lanterns, tansu cabinets, and fine furniture for the halls you will raise."
	]
	quest.143CCA59B9A0CD6B.quest_subtitle: "Carry power from wheel to wheel"
	quest.143CCA59B9A0CD6B.quest_desc: [
		"A tooth alone turns nothing. Power must travel."
		"Whittle shafts of andesite to bind one cogwheel to the next,"
		"and let the river drive your works through the water wheel."
	]
	quest.14434D1DCB23847B.quest_subtitle: "Walk the rakuichi, the free market"
	quest.14434D1DCB23847B.quest_desc: [
		"The rakuichi opens its stalls to any who carry coin, beholden to no lord's toll."
		"Trade with the village folk ten times over. Learn their wants, their seasons, their prices."
		"A merchant who knows the market knows where the next coin will fall."
	]
	quest.146FAB88F59D5D80.quest_subtitle: "Become the wall that does not fall"
	quest.146FAB88F59D5D80.quest_desc: [
		"Tate. The shield. The wall. The whole calling of the ashigaru is in one word."
		"You have stood, endured, and held when others ran. Now you are no longer a man in the line. You are the line."
		"Don the full armor of the footsoldier. Where you stand, the wall stands. Where the wall stands, Japan endures."
	]
	quest.1496048DCB579B4A.quest_subtitle: "Cut a stand of bamboo from the grove behind the field"
	quest.1496048DCB579B4A.quest_desc: [
		"Behind every paddy stands a grove of take, the bamboo that builds the village."
		"Cut a good supply: it makes scaffolds, baskets, water pipes, and the walls of a home."
		"Bamboo grows faster than any tree and never asks for much."
		"A wise farmer keeps the grove close. It feeds the hands as the rice feeds the belly."
	]
	quest.16E40843A6F9E5AE.quest_subtitle: "Kyūjutsu, the bow"
	quest.16E40843A6F9E5AE.quest_desc: [
		"The yumi strikes before an enemy can close the distance. Take up the bow, and the blade and the gun close to you forever."
		"You receive a bow, arrows, and points toward the Way of the Bow."
	]
	quest.177B0341599CA5FC.quest_subtitle: "Channel power through battle"
	quest.177B0341599CA5FC.quest_desc: [
		"Before a single sigil is drawn, the onmyōji must master the breath. Ki moves where the will sends it, and the will is forged in danger."
		"Cut down the restless dead. Each slain corpse teaches the lungs to hold steady when the night presses close."
		"Slay 15 zombie. The copper journal in your hand will not stay flimsy forever."
	]
	quest.19AEA436F48A7A99.quest_subtitle: "Unlock the Warrior's Path"
	quest.19AEA436F48A7A99.quest_desc: [
		"Carry a blade to the dōjō and kneel. Swear to walk the way of the bushi."
		"Then choose your weapon, for a warrior commits to a single art for life."
	]
	quest.1A8D7A2BAB60DF23.quest_subtitle: "Send your goods down the long road"
	quest.1A8D7A2BAB60DF23.quest_desc: [
		"A caravan moves where the lone peddler dares not, packhorse after packhorse along the highway."
		"Trade thirty times across the villages of the land and let your name travel ahead of your wares."
		"Gold flows to the house that keeps the roads busy."
	]
	quest.1ABE79B324156D68.quest_subtitle: "Shugendō, the mountain"
	quest.1ABE79B324156D68.quest_desc: [
		"Walk the sacred peaks, master the rites, and call upon the spirits of the dead. Choose Shugendō, and Onmyōdō closes to you."
		"You receive a spirit lantern and points toward the Way of the Mountain."
	]
	quest.1DB03F3393E7426C.quest_subtitle: "Arm yourself"
	quest.1DB03F3393E7426C.quest_desc: [
		"Even a farmer can lift a blade. Shape a simple sword and learn its weight in your hand."
		"Every master was once a beginner."
	]
	quest.1F04B7A079FE06ED.quest_subtitle: "Pray before the torii that stands in the sea"
	quest.1F04B7A079FE06ED.quest_desc: [
		"Itsukushima Jinja rises from the tide off the western shore, its great torii rooted in the waves."
		"Pilgrims wade the shallows at low water to stand beneath the vermilion gate."
		"Cross the inland sea and walk the shrine boards. Ask the kami of the strait for safe passage."
		"Seek the shrine near X -1988, Z 614 on the western coast."
	]
	quest.21DB5B7881631418.quest_subtitle: "The way of the master swordsmith"
	quest.21DB5B7881631418.quest_desc: [
		"Fold the steel a thousand times until the grain runs like water."
		"Complete the kaji tree and earn the title of tōkō, master swordsmith."
		"Take up the netherite katana, forged by your own hand."
	]
	quest.221E3A72A5172608.quest_subtitle: "Press the rice into form"
	quest.221E3A72A5172608.quest_desc: [
		"Rice is the wealth of the land. Cooked, salted, and pressed in the palm, it becomes nigiri the soldier can carry."
		"Shape four rice balls; a cook who masters rice need never see his people go hungry."
		"Prepare 4 Rice Balls."
	]
	quest.2476122B8AEFB44E.quest_subtitle: "Sixteen pieces of jade, weighed and counted"
	quest.2476122B8AEFB44E.quest_desc: [
		"Every house of trade begins with a single coin set aside."
		"Gather sixteen pieces of jade and learn the weight of wealth in your own hand."
		"From this first zeni a fortune is reckoned. Keep it, and let it breed more."
	]
	quest.2496F1D390C392D9.quest_subtitle: "The grand rite of the realm"
	quest.2496F1D390C392D9.quest_desc: [
		"Daijōsai is offered but once: the rite where the caster and the unseen world become one body, one breath, one will."
		"Complete the way of yin and yang in full, and the spirits acknowledge you as master."
		"Master the hijiri tree. The Ancient Codex, legendary ink, and a sheaf of scrolls are the realm's thanks."
	]
	quest.2672EC2C09059F52.quest_subtitle: "The long hunt of the far shot"
	quest.2672EC2C09059F52.quest_desc: [
		"A retainer is not made in a single dusk. Thirty skeletons fall before the bow becomes a part of the arm."
		"Range is patience worn as a skill. Hold the draw, read the wind, let the distant mark come to you."
		"Earn the steel a lord lends his archers, and you have earned your place upon the wall."
	]
	quest.26BDE64F238325D1.quest_subtitle: "Test your steel against worthy foes"
	quest.26BDE64F238325D1.quest_desc: [
		"A warrior tempered on the road must prove the edge his journey has ground upon him."
		"Seek out hard adversaries and cut them down without faltering or fleeing."
		"This is the heart of the shugyō: not to wander, but to be changed by the wandering and to win."
		"Twenty-five fell warriors, and not one step back."
	]
	quest.26D3151A313A2CCF.quest_subtitle: "Rise to gōshō, a great merchant of the realm"
	quest.26D3151A313A2CCF.quest_desc: [
		"The gōshō does not haggle in the stalls. The stalls send word to the gōshō."
		"Your warehouses brim, your ledgers run deep, and lesser houses borrow at your word."
		"You have mastered the way of commerce. Wealth bows to the one who commands its current."
	]
	quest.26FB7199484105D0.quest_subtitle: "Fill the coffers of the za"
	quest.26FB7199484105D0.quest_desc: [
		"The za, the trade guild, opens no doors to the empty-handed."
		"Bring four blocks of jade to the guild's coffers and buy your place among its members."
		"With the za behind you, the roads grow safer and the prices grow kinder."
	]
	quest.27C878805CC016C9.quest_subtitle: "Nyūbu, the entering of the peak"
	quest.27C878805CC016C9.quest_desc: [
		"The yamabushi do not pray in temples of the valley. Their dōjō is the bare ridge where the wind cuts and the snow does not melt."
		"Climb to the jagged peaks. Stand where earth ends and let the mountain weigh your spirit."
		"Only those who endure the high places may walk the way of Shugendō."
	]
	quest.2C451D1B90B72C81.quest_subtitle: "Climb the sacred peak of Fuji-san"
	quest.2C451D1B90B72C81.quest_desc: [
		"Fuji-san is the seat of the gods, a cone of fire and snow that all of Japan turns to face."
		"The ascetic climbs it to burn away the soft flesh of comfort and temper the spirit on the cold summit."
		"Set your feet on the slope and do not stop until the cinder cone is beneath you."
		"The mountain stands near X 3860, Z -570 in the eastern provinces."
	]
	quest.2EE614E206C03B09.quest_subtitle: "Master of the turning works"
	quest.2EE614E206C03B09.quest_desc: [
		"You have walked the whole way of mechanisms."
		"The precision mechanism, heart of every clever device, answers your hand."
		"Stand now as a karakuri-shi, a master of the unseen gears."
	]
	quest.2EE776508BB46ABA.quest_subtitle: "Kenjutsu, the sword"
	quest.2EE776508BB46ABA.quest_desc: [
		"The katana is the soul of the samurai. Take up the blade, and the bow and the gun close to you forever."
		"You receive your first katana and points toward the Way of the Sword."
	]
	quest.3095B4C374F68C84.quest_subtitle: "Words that bind the unseen"
	quest.3095B4C374F68C84.quest_desc: [
		"A mantra is not spoken. It is etched. Gather the blank scrolls on which the five elements will one day be bound."
		"An onmyōji who cannot prepare his own scrolls is no onmyōji at all."
		"Collect 4 Scroll."
	]
	quest.34B83A4F13BA6E7B.quest_subtitle: "Turn the blow aside and endure"
	quest.34B83A4F13BA6E7B.quest_desc: [
		"The ukedachi is the receiving stroke. To guard is not to flee; it is to take the blow on shield and steel and stand still standing."
		"Soak the strikes meant to fell you. Iron over the heart, the wall unbroken."
		"He who endures the first storm wins the field."
	]
	quest.350655219CA65817.quest_subtitle: "Lift your machines into the sky"
	quest.350655219CA65817.quest_desc: [
		"What turns upon the ground may yet rise above it."
		"Bind levitite to propeller and bearing and ride the high winds."
		"Take to the air, and carry your cannons where no road reaches."
	]
	quest.3AAAEDE083AAA0C8.quest_subtitle: "Master of the Blade"
	quest.3AAAEDE083AAA0C8.quest_desc: [
		"Spend your points and complete the Way of the Sword. When the final kata is yours, the realm will speak your name."
		"Take up the Netherite Odachi, a blade fit for a legend."
	]
	quest.3B18878846A59F2C.quest_subtitle: "Branches of the one art (optional)"
	quest.3B18878846A59F2C.quest_desc: [
		"The art has many ryūha. Some onmyōji walk the road of flame, some of lightning, some of the void beyond Yomi's gate."
		"Walk all three, if you dare carry their weight. The schools demand more blood than the trunk alone."
		"Slay 20 blaze. Three points of insight and two elemental tomes await the one who studies every branch."
	]
	quest.3C289424C673F15E.quest_subtitle: "Bear the daimyō's seal upon your shop curtain"
	quest.3C289424C673F15E.quest_desc: [
		"To be named goyō shōnin, purveyor to the daimyō, is to clothe and arm a province."
		"The castle's stores pass through your hands, and your noren bears the lord's own crest."
		"No higher honor is given a merchant. Serve the daimyō well, and the realm is your market."
	]
	quest.3E33AA1296B7888D.quest_subtitle: "Loose your first arrow in anger"
	quest.3E33AA1296B7888D.quest_desc: [
		"The yumi is taller than the man who draws it, yet a child can bend it once shown the way."
		"Take the bow to the bone-fields and let fly. Fifteen skeletons will teach the wrist what words cannot."
		"Every master once stood here, quiver shaking, learning that the arrow goes where the eye rests."
	]
	quest.4099620EDE8071D2.quest_subtitle: "Beat the metal until it holds"
	quest.4099620EDE8071D2.quest_desc: [
		"Raw iron is brittle. Worked iron is strong."
		"Press four blocks of iron, fold and temper them at the anvil."
		"A smith who cannot temper iron has no business near steel."
	]
	quest.40CDFAC0D055F9DD.quest_subtitle: "Train as the mounted archers do"
	quest.40CDFAC0D055F9DD.quest_desc: [
		"Yabusame is the old discipline: to ride at a gallop and strike a target while the world streams past."
		"First learn the moving shot on foot. Hunt the stray of the frozen wastes, fifteen in all."
		"Loose between heartbeats, between hoofbeats. The cold ones do not wait."
	]
	quest.40E0215AEDFDE097.quest_subtitle: "Satori, the awakening of the mountain saint"
	quest.40E0215AEDFDE097.quest_desc: [
		"At the gate of Yomi the saint stands without fear, for he has burned away all that death could take. The spirits know his name and come when he calls."
		"You have mastered the way of Shugendō."
		"Receive the Dictionary of Spirits and the trinity gem, that the unseen world answer to your hand."
	]
	quest.413867063AC6431B.quest_subtitle: "Hōjutsu, the gun"
	quest.413867063AC6431B.quest_desc: [
		"The tanegashima matchlock remade the art of war. Take up the gun, and the blade and the bow close to you forever."
		"You receive a hand cannon and points toward the Way of the Gun."
	]
	quest.44427792E21F7915.quest_subtitle: "Become the master of the kitchen"
	quest.44427792E21F7915.quest_desc: [
		"The itamae stands at the head of the kitchen, blade sure and dishes flawless. None question his table."
		"Master the hōchō discipline and earn the rank of itamae."
		"Complete the Hōchō mastery to claim the master's skillet."
	]
	quest.44B8C516D0F3C7C3.quest_subtitle: "Lay out the great table"
	quest.44B8C516D0F3C7C3.quest_desc: [
		"A victory deserves a feast. Set out fried rice, fish stew, and rolled rice so every guest leaves satisfied."
		"Plate three hearty dishes worthy of the lord's hall."
		"Provide Fried Rice, Fish Stew, and a Rice Roll."
	]
	quest.44F16C23A3DA5B25.quest_subtitle: "Practice without end"
	quest.44F16C23A3DA5B25.quest_desc: [
		"The blade is honed by repetition. Ten thousand cuts, and then ten thousand more."
		"Strike down the skeletal archers that haunt the night."
	]
	quest.45F18ED78F2912B8.quest_subtitle: "Unlock the Mystic's Path"
	quest.45F18ED78F2912B8.quest_desc: [
		"Carry a book into the sacred places and find one who reads the unseen."
		"Swear to walk the way of the hijiri. Then choose your tradition."
	]
	quest.464E038C5FDB4813.quest_subtitle: "The armorer's tribute in iron"
	quest.464E038C5FDB4813.quest_desc: [
		"A gunner stands exposed while he reloads. Plate of steel buys the seconds his hands need."
		"Offer iron to the forge so the smith may beat out a breastplate worthy of the firing line."
		"Surrender 4 blocks of iron and take up the ironclad's guard."
	]
	quest.468C0D1D8D675AED.quest_subtitle: "First blood"
	quest.468C0D1D8D675AED.quest_desc: [
		"Iaijutsu begins with the draw. Cut down the restless dead and learn the true weight of steel."
	]
	quest.47AAD499CE2EB5E2.quest_subtitle: "Odutsu, the great cannon of the daimyo"
	quest.47AAD499CE2EB5E2.quest_desc: [
		"Beyond the hand-gun lies the great cannon, the odutsu that breaks castle walls and turns a siege."
		"Unlock the hojutsu capstone and the foundry's secrets of Create: Big Cannons are yours."
		"Receive a starter kit of cannon-building parts and lay the first barrel of your own great gun."
	]
	quest.4A5BC21003370E88.quest_subtitle: "Master the mounted way"
	quest.4A5BC21003370E88.quest_desc: [
		"All the lane has led to this: the seat in the saddle, the arrow held loose, the target rushing near."
		"Complete your bushi training and take up the yumi as a true mounted archer of the field."
		"Ride, draw, loose. The way of the bow is finished, and only now begun."
	]
	quest.4B53F57FB4CB3163.quest_subtitle: "Raise the hall, lay the floor"
	quest.4B53F57FB4CB3163.quest_desc: [
		"Now the great work: the miyabushin, the temple-raising. Curved roof above, woven tatami below."
		"Gather a haul of tatami blocks for the floor of the prayer hall."
		"Reward: temple roofing, tatami matting, and two more daiku points."
	]
	quest.4EFFC3005AA1324C.quest_subtitle: "Black powder, the heart of the matchlock"
	quest.4EFFC3005AA1324C.quest_desc: [
		"The southern barbarians brought a strange black dust to Tanegashima, and with it a thunder no blade can answer."
		"Before the gun, there is the kayaku. Gather the powder and learn its weight in your hand."
		"Bring 16 gunpowder to begin the way of the hojutsushi."
	]
	quest.4F40F4F857297B6F.quest_subtitle: "Bring in a great mixed harvest beyond the rice alone"
	quest.4F40F4F857297B6F.quest_desc: [
		"A field of rice alone is a field one bad year from famine."
		"The careful noka plants the dry beds too: cabbage (kyabetsu) and onion stand against the lean months."
		"Gather a generous haul of both and prove the year a bountiful one."
		"When the storehouse holds many crops, no single failed harvest can starve the village."
	]
	quest.51F51949184EFFD9.quest_subtitle: "Take up the kitchen blade"
	quest.51F51949184EFFD9.quest_desc: [
		"Before broth, before rice, there is the hōchō. A cook who cannot keep an edge cannot feed an army."
		"Set a cutting board in your kitchen and learn to part flesh from bone with one clean stroke."
		"Craft a Cutting Board to begin the way of the kitchen blade."
	]
	quest.56BFEC62F77679CB.quest_subtitle: "Fell the timber and read the grain"
	quest.56BFEC62F77679CB.quest_desc: [
		"Every temple begins in the forest. The miyadaiku does not buy his wood; he chooses each tree, judges its grain, and saws it true."
		"Bring 32 logs to the workshop. Learn the saw before you learn the joint."
		"Reward: a saw, and your first step on the daiku path."
	]
	quest.58F225EA499047C1.quest_subtitle: "Cast brass and let the works run themselves"
	quest.58F225EA499047C1.quest_desc: [
		"Smelt copper with zinc to win brass, the metal of finer engines."
		"Bind it into casing and your contraptions gain memory and order."
		"Craft brass casing and the age of jidou, true automation, begins."
	]
	quest.5A5AA48B04AFFCFB.quest_subtitle: "The yari held shoulder to shoulder"
	quest.5A5AA48B04AFFCFB.quest_desc: [
		"One spear is a stick. A hundred spears, set as one, are the yaribusuma, the spear wall that no charge breaks."
		"Plant your feet. Level the point. Hold the line beside your fellows and meet what comes."
		"Cut down the oni that test your wall. Let none through."
	]
	quest.5D124A2BDA7419AE.quest_subtitle: "Draw the dashi from bone"
	quest.5D124A2BDA7419AE.quest_desc: [
		"Every great dish rests on its broth. Simmer bone and water until the kettle gives up its strength."
		"This dashi is the soul of the kitchen; from it come soups, stews, and noodle bowls fit for a daimyō."
		"Cook a pot of Bone Broth."
	]
	quest.605BA284F0D1E0D5.quest_subtitle: "Reap the golden ears when the heads grow heavy"
	quest.605BA284F0D1E0D5.quest_desc: [
		"Summer has fattened the grain and bowed each stalk toward the water."
		"Move down the rows with a steady hand and gather the harvested rice."
		"A full granary is the truest wealth a village can hold."
		"Bring in the crop before the autumn storms beat it into the mud."
	]
	quest.62282BC91365AAEC.quest_subtitle: "Onmyōdō, yin and yang"
	quest.62282BC91365AAEC.quest_desc: [
		"Read the stars, bind the spirits, and command the five elements. Choose Onmyōdō, and Shugendō closes to you."
		"You receive a spell book and points toward the Way of Yin and Yang."
	]
	quest.6366E10C02C1998D.quest_subtitle: "Tie on your sandals and take to the road"
	quest.6366E10C02C1998D.quest_desc: [
		"The musha shugyō begins when a warrior leaves the safety of walls and lords behind."
		"No master remains to teach you. The road itself is the dōjō now."
		"Cut down a foe that bars the highway, then set out with your blade and your wits."
		"Far shrines and far mountains await, and the self you carry there will not be the self that returns."
	]
	quest.6575034062A5DEA9.quest_subtitle: "Tanegashima no tatsujin, the lane's capstone"
	quest.6575034062A5DEA9.quest_desc: [
		"You have learned powder, nerve, and armor. Now the school names you a master gunner."
		"Complete the bushi mastery to claim the founding parts of a true bronze cannon."
	]
	quest.678341C5F4B2C136.quest_subtitle: "The pilgrimage is fulfilled, the warrior is made"
	quest.678341C5F4B2C136.quest_desc: [
		"You have prayed at Itsukushima, climbed Fuji-san, and crossed the ashes of Osore-zan."
		"You have shed blood on distant ground and returned with a steadier hand and a quieter heart."
		"The musha shugyō is complete. The road has finished the work no master could."
		"Take up the odachi of a true wanderer, and let the realm know a swordsman walks abroad."
	]
	quest.692DFA1DBFD8FEED.quest_subtitle: "The realm stirs"
	quest.692DFA1DBFD8FEED.quest_desc: [
		"You wake beneath an unfamiliar sky. The war-torn realm of 天空戦国 lies spread before you, its provinces at each other's throats."
		"Gather your wits. A long road waits."
	]
	quest.6BA1EC560ADA71E4.quest_subtitle: "Walk the mountain of the dead"
	quest.6BA1EC560ADA71E4.quest_desc: [
		"Osore-zan, the Mountain of Dread, smokes with sulfur in the cold far north."
		"Here the living come to speak with the departed across the river of the threshold."
		"Light incense among the barren stones and prove your nerve where lesser men turn back."
		"The grey mountain lies near X 6028, Z -7210 in the northern wastes."
	]
	quest.6DC05FE5A141146E.quest_subtitle: "Cut the first tooth of the gear"
	quest.6DC05FE5A141146E.quest_desc: [
		"The karakuri masters say all motion begins with the cogwheel."
		"Crush andesite with iron in the mixer and shape the alloy into toothed wheels."
		"Forge eight cogwheels and learn the rhythm of turning."
	]
	quest.6DE5D7D751E519B3.quest_subtitle: "Take up the shield and stand in the line"
	quest.6DE5D7D751E519B3.quest_desc: [
		"You are ashigaru. No great name, no fine horse. Only your two feet, the line beside you, and the wall you raise with your own arm."
		"Take up a shield. The man who can be moved is already dead. The man who holds is the wall."
		"Stand fast, and learn the heihō, the foot soldier's discipline."
	]
	quest.6E3F4A96B4B35B23.quest_subtitle: "Master the blast before you master the barrel"
	quest.6E3F4A96B4B35B23.quest_desc: [
		"The tanegashima matchlock is loud, slow, and unforgiving. A man who fears the flash will never hold the line."
		"Steady your nerve against the creeper's blast, the closest thing these lands offer to a misfired charge."
		"Fell 12 creepers and you will flinch no more when the powder roars."
	]
	quest.6FF891D55C9DF029.quest_subtitle: "The tome answers a steady hand"
	quest.6FF891D55C9DF029.quest_desc: [
		"Spellcraft is patience. The Ironbound Tome holds more than the copper journal ever could, but it answers only the disciplined caster."
		"Prove your discipline against the endless dead, and the deeper trunk of the art opens to you."
		"Slay 25 foes. With this milestone your training is ripe for the Grand Rite."
	]
	quest.701E52A08CD66693.quest_subtitle: "Strike like lightning"
	quest.701E52A08CD66693.quest_desc: [
		"A true swordsman ends a duel in a single breath. Hunt the crawling things and perfect the killing stroke."
		"You earn the steel armor of a sworn retainer."
	]
	quest.746DD4C8DE72CA47.quest_subtitle: "Fire, water, wood, metal, earth"
	quest.746DD4C8DE72CA47.quest_desc: [
		"Gogyō: the five phases turn one into the next without end. To command fire, first you must stand in its breath unburned."
		"The blaze of the lower world carries the phase of fire in its very bones. Read it, then end it."
		"Slay 10 blaze. A scroll of true working is yours when the smoke clears."
	]
	quest.757A638874919E5B.quest_subtitle: "Open the Ways"
	quest.757A638874919E5B.quest_desc: [
		"Press your skills key and behold the Ways (道), the paths of mastery open to you."
		"Quests pour points into your Ways. Spend them to grow in strength and craft."
		"Take these first points into Heihō, the footsoldier's discipline, and feel how it is done."
	]
	quest.763B6CDC748018F4.quest_subtitle: "Master of five hundred koku, lord of the harvest"
	quest.763B6CDC748018F4.quest_desc: [
		"Five hundred koku of rice: enough to feed a village for a year and still pay the daimyo's due."
		"You have walked every season, from the flooded planting to the heavy autumn sickle."
		"The way of the rice field holds no more secrets from you."
		"Take up this fine kama (hoe). You are now a master of the harvest, and the land answers to your hand."
	]
	quest.7855C54E2C1328AA.quest_subtitle: "Light the coals and raise the hammer"
	quest.7855C54E2C1328AA.quest_desc: [
		"Every blade begins as common iron and a hot fire."
		"Smelt and gather sixteen iron ingots to stock the kaji's forge."
		"From this iron the long road to the katana begins."
	]
	quest.785E916556B8C2A4.quest_subtitle: "The road forks"
	quest.785E916556B8C2A4.quest_desc: [
		"A warrior must find a calling. Some take up arms at a dōjō. Others seek a teacher in the high mountains."
		"Set out, and decide who you will become."
	]
	quest.78E1EAED17CA2C81.quest_subtitle: "Yobiyose, the calling-near"
	quest.78E1EAED17CA2C81.quest_desc: [
		"The smoke of the goma opens the road between worlds. From the high air the tengu answer, restless spirits drawn to the chant."
		"Strike down eight tengu and prove you can stand against what you summon."
		"Bind their essence in the fragile soul-gem before it scatters."
	]
	quest.7DB050E1B6EFBD97.quest_subtitle: "Yamabushi, one who lies down in the mountains"
	quest.7DB050E1B6EFBD97.quest_desc: [
		"Hardship is the whole of the teaching. The ascetic walks until his feet bleed and fights until his arms fail, seeking the death of the lesser self."
		"Cut down five-and-twenty foes upon the slopes."
		"From the crucible take the spirit-attuned crystal, hardened as you are hardened."
	]
