	quest.001B37D9696DD027.quest_subtitle: "Grind stone to powder with the turning wheel"
	quest.001B37D9696DD027.quest_desc: [
		"The simplest of mills needs no casing, only a wheel and a steady turn."
		"Set the millstone spinning and let it crush ore and grain to meal."
		"From dust comes flour, and from flour, bread for the long campaign."
	]
	quest.0117C3FE4AA4482B.quest_subtitle: "Cast the iron balls the cannon spits"
	quest.0117C3FE4AA4482B.quest_desc: [
		"Powder is only half the shot. Before the gun can answer, the foundry must pour the iron round that flies."
		"Cast shot balls in the mould and stack them by the breech."
		"Forge 16 shot balls, the plain round shot of every gunline."
	]
	quest.0194B39FEC1552BF.quest_subtitle: "Court death for the finest cut"
	quest.0194B39FEC1552BF.quest_desc: [
		"Fugu — the pufferfish whose flesh is prized and whose poison kills. Only a steady hand and a trusted blade may serve it."
		"To plate the pufferfish roll is to stake your reputation, and the diner's life, on your skill."
		"Prepare 2 Pufferfish Rolls."
	]
	quest.01F883898569E208.quest_subtitle: "Put the rival callers in the ground"
	quest.01F883898569E208.quest_desc: [
		"Not every wielder of the dead serves the realm. The necromancer raises corpses and bends them to spite."
		"Hunt down the grave-callers and scatter their puppets, twelve dark masters laid low."
		"Slay 12 Necromancer."
	]
	quest.02A97E9A6EA10D6F.quest_subtitle: "Ladle the everyday bowl"
	quest.02A97E9A6EA10D6F.quest_desc: [
		"Fermented bean paste dissolved in warm dashi — miso soup is the quiet companion to every meal in Japan."
		"Humble and warming, it sits beside the rice from a peasant's hut to a daimyō's hall."
		"Prepare 2 bowls of Miso Soup."
	]
	quest.036A0E3F11362AE5.quest_subtitle: "Stack the black-and-gold lacquer"
	quest.036A0E3F11362AE5.quest_desc: [
		"Layer upon patient layer the urushi sap is laid, until wood gleams like polished stone."
		"Gather sixteen lengths of lacquered keyaki, the luxury good that foreign ships cross oceans to buy."
	]
	quest.053664718D888599.quest_subtitle: "Put the gun on wheels"
	quest.053664718D888599.quest_desc: [
		"A cannon rooted to one spot is a target. Mount it on a carriage and the gun rolls where the battle turns."
		"The carriage bears the recoil and lets a crew wheel the great barrel into line."
		"Build a Cannon Carriage and take your artillery to the field."
	]
	quest.054EC5BAB94C23FC.quest_subtitle: "Don the mino to shed the mountain rains"
	quest.054EC5BAB94C23FC.quest_desc: [
		"Where the hat ends, the mino begins — a cape of layered straw that turns the cold rain from your shoulders."
		"Hat and cape together make the silhouette of the wanderer, hunched against the weather of a hundred ri."
	]
	quest.05B70CD693EB0C36.quest_subtitle: "Forge the legendary blade of scarlet metal"
	quest.05B70CD693EB0C36.quest_desc: [
		"Hihi'irokane, the scarlet metal of myth, surrenders to none but the master smith."
		"Fold it into the tamahagane and forge the ōdachi that legends are written about."
		"This is the smith's masterpiece — a blade that will outlive its maker and his name."
	]
	quest.05D21C06A57E3CBE.quest_subtitle: "Fell a mounted man with a footsoldier's spear"
	quest.05D21C06A57E3CBE.quest_desc: [
		"Kabutokubi, the helmeted head, was the prize that raised a poor ashigaru's name above his birth."
		"A samurai is worth ten footsoldiers; bring him down with the spear-wall and the reward is yours."
		"Take the heads of eight samurai, and let the captains learn your name."
	]
	quest.087ECF07B1908063.quest_subtitle: "Slake the lime, smooth the wall"
	quest.087ECF07B1908063.quest_desc: [
		"Shikkui is lime plaster burnished to a soft white sheen, cool in summer and proof against fire."
		"Mix and trowel sakura shikkui across the timber frame until the surface is smooth as still water."
		"Reward: extra shikkui for the rooms still bare."
	]
	quest.09566C08866EF790.quest_subtitle: "Take up the axe and gather your first wood"
	quest.09566C08866EF790.quest_desc: [
		"Every road in this realm begins with the forest."
		"Fell a few trees and gather their logs; from wood come the workbench, the haft, and the home."
		"Even a daimyō's castle began as a single felled tree."
	]
	quest.09844067C9215F37.quest_subtitle: "Pour the first cup for the gods of the harvest"
	quest.09844067C9215F37.quest_desc: [
		"The first sake of the season is omiki, poured at the shrine for the kami who guard the fields."
		"Brew and bottle a good store of rice wine; what the gods do not drink, the village shares at festival."
		"From a single grain of rice to a cup raised in thanks, the year has come full circle."
		"Reward: fermented sake, stronger for the waiting."
	]
	quest.0A34BA56AE17FA76.quest_subtitle: "Hoard gold to barter beyond the border"
	quest.0A34BA56AE17FA76.quest_desc: [
		"Karamono, goods from abroad, pass through hands that take no copper mon, only bright gold."
		"Amass thirty-two ingots to barter with the keneō who trade across the burning frontier."
	]
	quest.0A9E1680284D7ED2.quest_subtitle: "The sword-saint's edge"
	quest.0A9E1680284D7ED2.quest_desc: [
		"The kensei, the sword-saint, carries a blade folded by a master's hand and quenched in a master's patience. To hold it is to inherit a lineage."
		"Forge the Blade of the Kensei, the truest katana these provinces can yield."
		"Two points and a measure of jewel steel reward the one who reaches this peak."
	]
	quest.0ADFB6534D8DEADE.quest_subtitle: "Clear the hills of the robber bands"
	quest.0ADFB6534D8DEADE.quest_desc: [
		"The sanzoku descend from the hills when the rice is heavy and the guard is thin."
		"Drive twenty bandits from the province with the bow before they reach the granaries."
		"A village remembers the archer who kept the harvest in their bowls."
	]
	quest.0B274E6DD87DD0A7.quest_subtitle: "Crown the warrior's head"
	quest.0B274E6DD87DD0A7.quest_desc: [
		"The kabuto is more than iron over the skull; it is the face a samurai shows to death. Lacquered, crested, and fearsome."
		"Forge the Daimyo Kabuto and take your place among the armored lords."
		"A matching kusazuri is given to gird your stride."
	]
	quest.0E290057B75B86F2.quest_subtitle: "Clear the hills of brigands"
	quest.0E290057B75B86F2.quest_desc: [
		"Where law is thin, bandits thicken. They take the harvest the daimyō does not, and leave less behind."
		"The ashigaru's first duty in peace is the same as in war: hold the ground and keep the weak unharmed."
		"Hunt down fifteen bandits and make the roads safe."
	]
	quest.0FB6196D1542BF1B.quest_subtitle: "A standing lantern for the garden path"
	quest.0FB6196D1542BF1B.quest_desc: [
		"The tōrō stands silent along the approach, its single flame marking the way to the shrine."
		"Set pagoda lanterns of tiered stone to light the garden and the temple precinct."
		"Reward: a white pagoda lantern, and a daiku point."
	]
	quest.111DAED6577227DE.quest_subtitle: "Channel the fire through pyrium"
	quest.111DAED6577227DE.quest_desc: [
		"A staff is a spine for the spell, focusing what the bare hand would let scatter."
		"Take up the Pyrium Staff, forged of fire-touched metal, and let your flame strike true and far."
		"Obtain the Pyrium Staff."
	]
	quest.12A81C2A41C30A2E.quest_subtitle: "Raise the prized melon in the summer sun"
	quest.12A81C2A41C30A2E.quest_desc: [
		"The suika swells fat and sweet on the vine through the long summer days."
		"Tend the patch and cut the ripe fruit, prized above all in the heat of the seventh month."
		"A perfect melon is a gift fit for a lord; lesser ones cool the field hands at noon."
	]
	quest.1466336DE9665086.quest_subtitle: "Lay out a bench to work upon"
	quest.1466336DE9665086.quest_desc: [
		"Bare hands shape little. A craftsman needs a place to work."
		"Set your planks into a crafting table, and the patterns of a thousand tools open to you."
	]
	quest.15C733FE66F0F370.quest_subtitle: "Pull the glowing kera from the tatara's broken walls"
	quest.15C733FE66F0F370.quest_desc: [
		"The tatara burns for three days and nights, swallowing satetsu and charcoal."
		"When the clay furnace is broken open, the kera — the raw bloom of tamahagane — is dragged from the embers."
		"Win six lumps of raw tamahagane; the living steel still sleeps within."
	]
	quest.165BBCE9FA2321EA.quest_subtitle: "The southern barbarians' hardest steel"
	quest.165BBCE9FA2321EA.quest_desc: [
		"Beyond steel lies nethersteel, quenched in the fires of the lower world. No charge yet packed has split a barrel forged of it."
		"This is the metal of siege guns and the heaviest mortars, won only by those who brave the nether's heat."
		"Smith 8 nethersteel ingots for the guns that break castle walls."
	]
	quest.16D45D5ED42F0A62.quest_subtitle: "Clear the highways of brigands"
	quest.16D45D5ED42F0A62.quest_desc: [
		"The roads of a divided land crawl with masterless men who take by force what they will not earn."
		"Put down the bandits who prey on travelers, and let honest folk pass in peace."
		"Slay 5 Bandits."
	]
	quest.18BE867921047AC5.quest_subtitle: "Pile six blocks of gold in the strongbox"
	quest.18BE867921047AC5.quest_desc: [
		"The senryōbako, the thousand-ryō chest, is the strongbox of the truly rich, bound in iron and never opened lightly."
		"Stack six blocks of gold within and let your house be counted among the wealthy of the realm."
	]
	quest.1A4BFF6DF127C5FF.quest_subtitle: "Weigh sixteen koban of bright gold"
	quest.1A4BFF6DF127C5FF.quest_desc: [
		"Above the copper mon gleams the koban, an oval of pressed gold that buys a season's rice."
		"Gather sixteen and you carry the weight of a samurai's stipend in a single pouch."
	]
	quest.1BABE988E1BC865B.quest_subtitle: "Grind the stick, wet the stone"
	quest.1BABE988E1BC865B.quest_desc: [
		"Cheap ink fades, and a fading talisman is a lie told to the spirits. The careful caster grinds finer ink for finer work."
		"Refine your craft until rare ink flows black and unbroken from the brush."
		"Gather 4 Rare Ink."
	]
	quest.1C19A7D13FBAB074.quest_subtitle: "Gather the black river-sand that feeds the tatara"
	quest.1C19A7D13FBAB074.quest_desc: [
		"Before steel there is sand — satetsu, the iron-bearing grains washed down from the mountains."
		"Pan sixteen measures of the dark iron sand from riverbeds and dunes."
		"From this black grit the tatara furnace draws all of its iron."
	]
	quest.1C591DCE9A3FDD24.quest_subtitle: "Reach a village far from where you began"
	quest.1C591DCE9A3FDD24.quest_desc: [
		"The shugyō is measured in distance as much as in blood."
		"Walk until the dialect changes and the faces are strangers' — stand in the streets of a village far from your own."
		"Take a blank map at the headman's gate and begin to chart the road behind you."
	]
	quest.1C696378E17460EF.quest_subtitle: "Bore the barrel true with Create's power"
	quest.1C696378E17460EF.quest_desc: [
		"A cast barrel is solid metal until the drill carves its throat. Set the cannon drill against the bore and let the kinetics of Create grind it smooth."
		"An untrue bore sends the shot wild; a clean one sends it where the eye points."
		"Craft a Cannon Drill and bore your barrels to a mirror finish."
	]
	quest.1D01C3BE962CEFBB.quest_subtitle: "Open the ledger of commerce"
	quest.1D01C3BE962CEFBB.quest_desc: [
		"The merchant bows low, but his abacus rules the province as surely as any sword."
		"Strike a bargain with a villager and learn how jade changes hands in the wider realm."
		"Trade with a villager."
	]
	quest.1D0CB6881B589C39.quest_subtitle: "Oi, the box-pack of the wandering ascetic"
	quest.1D0CB6881B589C39.quest_desc: [
		"Upon his back the yamabushi bears the oi, a woven pack that carries altar, scroll, and provision across a hundred mountains."
		"Weave the basket-pack and shoulder the whole of your practice."
		"What a man can carry, a man can never lose."
	]
	quest.1D489C9CFDD9C73A.quest_subtitle: "Train the southern vine up its bamboo poles"
	quest.1D489C9CFDD9C73A.quest_desc: [
		"The tomato came late on the southern barbarians' ships, but it has found a home in the warm beds."
		"Tie the heavy vines to bamboo stakes and let the red fruit ripen in the sun."
		"Gather a generous picking; the bamboo you cut already stands ready as its trellis."
	]
	quest.1E73C1C3773B9EFF.quest_subtitle: "Outpace the marching column"
	quest.1E73C1C3773B9EFF.quest_desc: [
		"The messenger who rides arrives before the army that walks."
		"Lay a saddle across a willing mount, and the distances of the realm shrink beneath the hooves."
		"Obtain a Saddle."
	]
	quest.205BA663E19548C9.quest_subtitle: "Set a whole structure turning"
	quest.205BA663E19548C9.quest_desc: [
		"A shaft turns a wheel, but a bearing turns a world."
		"Anchor a mechanical bearing, glue your build to its face, and watch it revolve as one body."
		"Windmills, gates, and rotating halls all begin here."
	]
	quest.20A82A3FBCFF9329.quest_subtitle: "The blade that sweeps the whole rank"
	quest.20A82A3FBCFF9329.quest_desc: [
		"Where the yari thrusts, the naginata reaps. Its curved blade is swung in wide arcs that cut the legs from a charge."
		"Sōhei monks and temple guards favored it; a single sweep clears a doorway or a horse's path."
		"Shape a naginata and learn the cut that answers the thrust."
	]
	quest.20BE23EB72E1B753.quest_subtitle: "Forge the point in folded steel"
	quest.20BE23EB72E1B753.quest_desc: [
		"Wood splinters; tamahagane endures. The smith folds the steel until the grain runs true and the edge will not roll."
		"Fit a head of tamahagane to your shaft. The same length, the same stance, but now the point bites through lacquer and bone alike."
	]
	quest.229BEAF6B98B3606.quest_subtitle: "The studded club of legend"
	quest.229BEAF6B98B3606.quest_desc: [
		"Oni carry the kanabō, and so do the men brave enough to fight as oni do. Iron-studded, unsubtle, and crushing."
		"Forge a Kanabō. There is no parry for a weapon that needs no edge."
	]
	quest.240CD9AECEE2AC65.quest_subtitle: "Gather the feathers that steer the flight"
	quest.240CD9AECEE2AC65.quest_desc: [
		"An arrow without feathers tumbles like a falling leaf and strikes nothing."
		"Take sixteen feathers from the birds of the field; these are the rudder of every shaft."
		"The fletcher knows: it is the tail, not the head, that decides where the arrow goes."
	]
	quest.278C4AF780BDC3CD.quest_subtitle: "Descend and break the living rock"
	quest.278C4AF780BDC3CD.quest_desc: [
		"Beneath the soil waits stone, patient and plentiful."
		"Mine cobble and bind it to a haft. Stone tools bite deeper and tire less than wood."
		"Now the earth begins to answer you."
	]
	quest.2863A45C9396D584.quest_subtitle: "Build a chest to keep what you gather"
	quest.2863A45C9396D584.quest_desc: [
		"A warrior who carries everything carries nothing well."
		"Craft a chest and store your goods safely. An ordered storehouse is the start of a settled life."
	]
	quest.28F21B6054511D63.quest_subtitle: "Sharpen the spear of the common soldier"
	quest.28F21B6054511D63.quest_desc: [
		"The yari is the first weapon set in an ashigaru's hands, and the last he sets down."
		"A shaft of wood, a point of will. Reach is the poor man's armor; keep the foe at the spear's length and he can never touch you."
		"Cut and bind a wooden yari, and learn why a wall of points turns away horses."
	]
	quest.291C9BCFB855DCC2.quest_subtitle: "Preserve the garden in salt"
	quest.291C9BCFB855DCC2.quest_desc: [
		"Tsukemono — vegetables pressed in salt and rice bran until sharp and crisp. They keep through winter and wake a tired palate."
		"A side of pickles turns plain rice into a meal a soldier will remember."
		"Make 4 Pickles."
	]
	quest.2974D353AAC92E6D.quest_subtitle: "Raise the bench of the arrow-smith"
	quest.2974D353AAC92E6D.quest_desc: [
		"The yashi, the arrow-maker, does not work upon his knee."
		"Set up the fletching table, the proper bench where heads are seated and shafts run true."
		"With a craftsman's station, the making of arrows becomes a discipline, not a chore."
	]
	quest.29EDC4F849FFC757.quest_subtitle: "Gather the daizu, the bean behind every broth"
	quest.29EDC4F849FFC757.quest_desc: [
		"The daizu, the soybean, is the quiet foundation of the whole kitchen."
		"From it come miso, shōyu, tofu, and nattō; without it the pot stands empty."
		"Gather a basket of beans and set them by to ferment into miso."
		"Reward: a bowl of miso soup, the morning comfort of every home."
	]
	quest.29F94703FCBD83D5.quest_subtitle: "Set the mato upon the range"
	quest.29F94703FCBD83D5.quest_desc: [
		"The mato, the straw target, suffers ten thousand arrows without complaint."
		"Raise a target block upon your range and drill the draw until it is wordless habit."
		"Skill is not won in battle; it is only spent there. It is won here, at the practice butt."
	]
	quest.2A600A89322A7B6F.quest_subtitle: "Shinka, the cold flame of the other world"
	quest.2A600A89322A7B6F.quest_desc: [
		"There is a fire that does not warm and does not consume, blue as a drowned star. The adept kindles it to purify what iron cannot touch."
		"Light the spiritfire and pass your offerings through its strange and patient burning."
		"Receive white altar candles to carry its light into the dark halls."
	]
	quest.2AACB4605CB4EB43.quest_subtitle: "Kō, the smoke that carries the prayer"
	quest.2AACB4605CB4EB43.quest_desc: [
		"Kindle the incense before the rock-cut shrine, that its thin thread of smoke may climb to where the voice cannot reach."
		"Gather eight bundles of incense and lay them upon the altar stone."
		"The kami lean close to the fragrance and listen."
	]
	quest.2B3A218C4142DE0A.quest_subtitle: "Turn the harvest into strength"
	quest.2B3A218C4142DE0A.quest_desc: [
		"Raw grain is mere promise. Set the pot over the fire and let the steam rise."
		"A bowl of cooked rice steadies the hand and clears the mind for whatever the day demands."
		"Prepare 4 Cooked Rice."
	]
	quest.2BA19E928B00D575.quest_subtitle: "Boil water into boundless power"
	quest.2BA19E928B00D575.quest_desc: [
		"When river and windmill no longer suffice, raise steam."
		"Fire a boiler beneath a steam engine and let pressure drive your greatest works."
		"This is the heart that beats beneath an empire of brass."
	]
	quest.2C1CBF69C0156A37.quest_subtitle: "Tama-chōchin, the lamp for wandering souls"
	quest.2C1CBF69C0156A37.quest_desc: [
		"On the night roads the dead lose their way. The ascetic hangs a soul lantern at the trailhead, a small blue flame to call them home."
		"Craft the soul paper lantern and set it burning against the dark."
		"Where its light falls, no lost spirit walks alone."
	]
	quest.2C8EACAE71FC1A02.quest_subtitle: "Cut down the lordless swords that prey on the road"
	quest.2C8EACAE71FC1A02.quest_desc: [
		"A rōnin is a samurai whose lord has fallen, his stipend gone, his oath dissolved. Some keep their honor; many turn to the road."
		"These masterless blades waylay villages and travelers alike. The discipline of the line has no place for them."
		"Drive ten rōnin from the province."
	]
	quest.2D0520FDEBCAB54C.quest_subtitle: "Marry vinegared rice and fish"
	quest.2D0520FDEBCAB54C.quest_desc: [
		"Vinegared rice pressed beneath a sliver of fish — sushi is precision made edible, the cook's discipline laid bare."
		"Each piece must be shaped in a single breath, neither too tight nor too loose."
		"Prepare 4 Sushi."
	]
	quest.2DA8FF4557E10403.quest_subtitle: "Descend the slope to the burning underworld"
	quest.2DA8FF4557E10403.quest_desc: [
		"Yomotsu Hirasaka is the slope that joins the world of the living to the land of the dead."
		"Step through the fire-gate into the burning hells, where the ash falls like grey snow and nothing living should walk."
		"Carry fire-warding sake, and do not look back as you cross the threshold."
	]
	quest.2E2B811814A8E7FF.quest_subtitle: "The blade worn closest"
	quest.2E2B811814A8E7FF.quest_desc: [
		"The tantō is the dagger a bushi never sets aside, for close work, for honor, for the last resort no warrior speaks aloud."
		"Forge a Tamahagane Tantō. Short steel, but no less sacred than the long."
	]
	quest.2E35F79E7DB9BC08.quest_subtitle: "Carry a chōchin to light the night road"
	quest.2E35F79E7DB9BC08.quest_desc: [
		"The road does not stop at dusk, and the mountain passes are black as ink."
		"Carry a folding paper lantern to throw a small circle of light against the dark — and against what moves in it."
	]
	quest.2EA67EF02761E5C5.quest_subtitle: "Plate the dō, the cuirass of the samurai"
	quest.2EA67EF02761E5C5.quest_desc: [
		"The smith forges armor as readily as blades."
		"Lace and rivet the dō, the lamellar cuirass that guards a warrior's chest and belly."
		"Worn by the daimyo's retainers, it turns aside the arrow and the glancing cut."
	]
	quest.2F654C03F7490860.quest_subtitle: "Claim the wanderer-warrior's storied blade"
	quest.2F654C03F7490860.quest_desc: [
		"The nobushi were the wild warriors of the hills, half-soldier and half-bandit, who lived and died by the naginata."
		"Their finest blades passed from hand to hand on the field, taken from the fallen and carried on."
		"Win the Naginata of the Nobushi, and let the long road of the footsoldier reach its end in your grip."
	]
	quest.3155D36FFB0CE885.quest_subtitle: "A paper moon at the gate"
	quest.3155D36FFB0CE885.quest_desc: [
		"When dusk settles on the temple road, the chōchin glows like a small caught moon."
		"Fold paper over a bamboo frame and hang four lanterns to light the way for night travellers."
		"Reward: white paper lanterns, and a daiku point."
	]
	quest.319EF8A72650FB2A.quest_subtitle: "Mandarage, the flower of visions"
	quest.319EF8A72650FB2A.quest_desc: [
		"The datura blooms where the path grows thin, its fruit a door into dreaming. The ascetic eats of it and walks among the spirits awake."
		"Harvest eight of the demon's dream fruit from the mountain herb-beds."
		"Tread its visions with care, for not all who enter them return whole."
	]
	quest.3209E2F5918580B2.quest_subtitle: "Read the road the spirits hide"
	quest.3209E2F5918580B2.quest_desc: [
		"Onmyōdō is not only striking; it is seeing. The diviner reads what is hidden in earth and distance."
		"Carry a Wayward Compass and let it point you toward the secrets the land keeps."
		"Obtain the Wayward Compass."
	]
	quest.324F8F95461CD654.quest_subtitle: "Weave the sedge hat that shades every field-hand"
	quest.324F8F95461CD654.quest_desc: [
		"The sugegasa, woven from sedge and straw, turns the summer sun and the autumn rain alike."
		"Weave one for yourself; it is the crown of the noka, worn from planting to harvest."
		"Reward: a straw cape, that neither downpour nor cold wind will drive you from the rows."
	]
	quest.332F2EB4BE388BF6.quest_subtitle: "Clad yourself in jewel steel"
	quest.332F2EB4BE388BF6.quest_desc: [
		"From the tatara's heat comes the dō, the cuirass that turns aside the careless blow."
		"Buckle it on. Iron between you and the world is iron well spent."
		"Forge and equip a Tamahagane Dō."
	]
	quest.3380BB3BE3F6DD2E.quest_subtitle: "Bruises before blood"
	quest.3380BB3BE3F6DD2E.quest_desc: [
		"No student touches live steel on the first day. The bokken, the wooden blade, teaches the hands before the edge can betray them."
		"Carve a wooden odachi and drill until the form is true. Wood breaks bone as surely as steel breaks flesh."
	]
	quest.343195BB775F1775.quest_subtitle: "Many small shots where one great one served"
	quest.343195BB775F1775.quest_desc: [
		"Where the great cannon speaks once and slow, the autocannon stammers a hail of brass cartridges without pause."
		"Each round is crimped, filled, and belted ready for the breech's hungry pace."
		"Load 16 autocannon cartridges and learn the rhythm of rapid fire."
	]
	quest.37BEED6D59538789.quest_subtitle: "Cull the marsh-dead and their venom arrows"
	quest.37BEED6D59538789.quest_desc: [
		"From the wet reeds rise the swamp-dead, loosing arrows tipped with creeping poison."
		"Fifteen of these venomous archers must fall before the marsh is yours."
		"Learn to close the distance before their bows learn to close it on you."
	]
	quest.38912F3C516DD314.quest_subtitle: "Forge a tantō, your first true blade"
	quest.38912F3C516DD314.quest_desc: [
		"A warrior is known by the steel he carries. Begin with the tantō, the short blade kept close at hand."
		"Forge one with your own iron and wear it always."
		"It is a humble start, yet every legend of the sword begins with a first edge drawn."
	]
	quest.39004B00A9D873F0.quest_subtitle: "Smelt your first iron from the ore"
	quest.39004B00A9D873F0.quest_desc: [
		"Iron is the spine of every blade, plough, and bucket in the realm."
		"Smelt a handful of ingots in your new furnace."
		"From this dull grey metal, the long road to tamahagane begins."
	]
	quest.3957AD92BF8A0A66.quest_subtitle: "Break the crossbow bands of the road"
	quest.3957AD92BF8A0A66.quest_desc: [
		"Masterless footmen turned brigand haunt the highways, crossbows cocked for any traveler."
		"Hunt down fifteen of these outlaw ashigaru and make the roads safe again."
		"An arrow answers a bolt; trade them, and see whose aim is the truer."
	]
	quest.3A61F14D8B0AF22C.quest_subtitle: "Let the goods walk without hands"
	quest.3A61F14D8B0AF22C.quest_desc: [
		"No workshop runs on wheels alone; goods must travel between them."
		"String a mechanical belt from shaft to shaft and set funnels to feed and draw."
		"Now the contraption carries its own burden, and your hands are free."
	]
	quest.3A80D6E0D9E6069F.quest_subtitle: "Reishi, the eyes that see the unseen"
	quest.3A80D6E0D9E6069F.quest_desc: [
		"The world is thronged with things the common eye slides past. Grind the infused lenses and set them in a frame to look upon them at last."
		"Don the otherworld goggles and the hidden ores, the lurking spirits, all stand revealed."
		"To see truly is the first discipline of the saint."
	]
	quest.3AB41662A8FE97A4.quest_subtitle: "Where the brush meets the vellum"
	quest.3AB41662A8FE97A4.quest_desc: [
		"No ofuda is born in the field. It is born at the desk, where ink, brush, and blank parchment wait in silent order."
		"Raise an Inscription Table, the onmyōji's writing altar, and learn to bind spell to scroll with your own hand."
		"Place the Inscription Table."
	]
	quest.3CDBD022A559BE47.quest_subtitle: "Carve a bokutō and learn the great blade's balance"
	quest.3CDBD022A559BE47.quest_desc: [
		"No apprentice touches steel before wood."
		"Carve a wooden ōdachi and swing it ten thousand times to learn the weight and reach of the long blade."
		"Form must live in the hands before the forge will answer."
	]
	quest.3D1AF6F2A709A2E4.quest_subtitle: "Pull the long white roots from the dry bed"
	quest.3D1AF6F2A709A2E4.quest_desc: [
		"Beside the flooded paddy lies the dry bed, where the daikon drives its long white root deep into the loosened earth."
		"Pull a good harvest of the radish; salted in rice bran it feeds the household through the snows."
		"No farm table in Japan is set without the crisp white root."
	]
	quest.3D9D9C516C37BA96.quest_subtitle: "A storm of iron for massed ranks"
	quest.3D9D9C516C37BA96.quest_desc: [
		"Against a charging line, one ball is a poor answer. Bind a sack of small shot and the cannon becomes a scythe."
		"The grapeshot scatters wide, tearing through ashigaru and oni alike at close range."
		"Bag 8 loads of grapeshot for the day the enemy comes too near."
	]
	quest.3DB0527D3ACDA1DD.quest_subtitle: "From black sand, the soul of the blade"
	quest.3DB0527D3ACDA1DD.quest_desc: [
		"Before the smith, before the fire, there is the sand. The rivers of the old country run black with iron, and the tatara furnace hungers for it."
		"Gather sixteen measures of iron sand. From this humble grit the gods of the forge wake tamahagane, the jewel steel."
	]
	quest.3E28D9A7AD8DEED6.quest_subtitle: "Raise the kabuto, the crested war-helm"
	quest.3E28D9A7AD8DEED6.quest_desc: [
		"Above the dō sits the kabuto, the great helm of riveted iron plates."
		"Forge it with its flaring neck-guard and proud crest to crown the samurai."
		"A lord is known across the field by the silhouette of his kabuto."
	]
	quest.3ECCCECD32CF5242.quest_subtitle: "Raise the kitchen fire"
	quest.3ECCCECD32CF5242.quest_desc: [
		"No dish is born without flame. Set a stove of clay and iron so pot and skillet may rest above a steady fire."
		"From this hearth comes broth, rice, and every grilled thing the lord's table demands."
		"Build a Stove."
	]
	quest.3F28CE2889761B81.quest_subtitle: "One arm to tend many stations"
	quest.3F28CE2889761B81.quest_desc: [
		"Where the deployer is a single hand, the arm reaches across the whole bench."
		"Teach a mechanical arm its inputs and outputs, and it will sort and ferry without rest."
		"The clever master sets it once and walks away."
	]
	quest.4007C4901922B145.quest_subtitle: "Clear the highway of the bandits who prey on it"
	quest.4007C4901922B145.quest_desc: [
		"The nobushi lie in wait at the lonely bends of the road, falling on merchants and pilgrims alike."
		"Cut down fifteen of these highway brigands and make the road a little safer for those who follow."
	]
	quest.403325FA289F79F7.quest_subtitle: "Forge an edge worthy of the kitchen"
	quest.403325FA289F79F7.quest_desc: [
		"The flint blade serves the desperate, but the itamae deserves steel. Hammer iron to a fine edge and feel the difference in every cut."
		"A true knife parts fish from bone without bruising the flesh — the first mark of a real cook."
		"Craft an Iron Knife."
	]
	quest.4045E21B4F8E1F14.quest_subtitle: "String thirty-two mon upon the cord"
	quest.4045E21B4F8E1F14.quest_desc: [
		"Beneath the gold and jade of the great houses runs the humble mon, the copper coin of the common purse."
		"Gather thirty-two pieces and learn that no fortune is too small to begin counting."
	]
	quest.41B9C473EB36A660.quest_subtitle: "Crown the roll with glittering roe"
	quest.41B9C473EB36A660.quest_desc: [
		"Tobiko — flying-fish roe, bright orange beads that pop against the tongue and crown the finest rolls."
		"A garnish of roe marks a cook who spares no detail for the lord's pleasure."
		"Roll 2 Tobiko Rolls."
	]
	quest.42A623FAA62A1BF2.quest_subtitle: "Draw the circle no harm may cross"
	quest.42A623FAA62A1BF2.quest_desc: [
		"The kekkai is the barrier the caster sets between himself and the hungry dark."
		"Etch protective runes and learn to throw a ward about your body before the first blow lands."
		"Gather 4 Protective Rune."
	]
	quest.433A1D5A2D723E64.quest_subtitle: "Forge the tantō, the warrior's close companion"
	quest.433A1D5A2D723E64.quest_desc: [
		"Not every blade is long. The tantō is the dagger carried close — for the press of the melee and the warrior's rites."
		"Forge and grind a tantō to ride beside the longer steel."
		"A short blade, but one a samurai is never without."
	]
	quest.44B07BB811673B3E.quest_subtitle: "Walk among the realm's people"
	quest.44B07BB811673B3E.quest_desc: [
		"A lord is nothing without subjects, a road nothing without those who travel it."
		"Seek out a village and stand within its lanes, where rice is traded and rumor flies faster than any horse."
		"Find a village."
	]
	quest.4662CF036ED4F2A0.quest_subtitle: "Shape the great bow with your own hands"
	quest.4662CF036ED4F2A0.quest_desc: [
		"Before the arrow flies, the bow must be born: a stave of supple wood, three lengths of taut string."
		"Bend the wood and bind the cord until the yumi answers your pull."
		"No archer borrows his bow. Craft your own, and it becomes an arm you were not born with."
	]
	quest.46B94E7C1D378BAE.quest_subtitle: "Lay the iron road across the provinces"
	quest.46B94E7C1D378BAE.quest_desc: [
		"The kaidō roads bound the old realm; now iron rails will bind the new."
		"Raise a train station, lay track from province to province, and assemble a locomotive of your own design."
		"Carry goods and warriors the length of the land while you sit at ease."
	]
	quest.4757F9C22730A684.quest_subtitle: "Stir the basin and brew new alloys"
	quest.4757F9C22730A684.quest_desc: [
		"Heat and motion married above a basin yield what no forge alone can make."
		"Lower the mechanical mixer over a basin and compound your reagents."
		"From the swirling brew rise alloys, brass, and the stuff of finer engines."
	]
	quest.47A0D4E397266336.quest_subtitle: "Measure out a koku of grain"
	quest.47A0D4E397266336.quest_desc: [
		"In this age a lord's worth is reckoned not in coin but in koku, the rice that feeds a man for a year."
		"Gather sixty-four measures of rice, the true currency upon which every domain is weighed."
	]
	quest.47AA48D60D98B24F.quest_subtitle: "Take the head, end the war"
	quest.47AA48D60D98B24F.quest_desc: [
		"A war ends when a banner falls. Cut your way to the enemy warlord through his guard and take the head that rallies the field."
		"This is the soldier's highest deed and the swordsman's truest test."
		"Two points and the spoils of victory crown the one who returns from the warlord's tent."
	]
	quest.47C5147BD43E5E35.quest_subtitle: "Shirasu-kabe, white against the tile"
	quest.47C5147BD43E5E35.quest_desc: [
		"The white shirasu-kabe wall is the face a manor turns to the road, bright between dark beams and grey tile."
		"Finish the plastered walls in shirasu and let the hall stand proud as any castle keep."
		"Reward: shirasu-kabe panels, and a daiku point."
	]
	quest.4841EC81CE942099.quest_subtitle: "Earn a bow worthy of your name"
	quest.4841EC81CE942099.quest_desc: [
		"A master outgrows the plain stave and seeks a meika, a named and storied bow."
		"Forge the fine bow of deep-sea metal, swifter and surer than any common yumi."
		"Carry it, and let the realm learn the name of the one who draws it."
		"Two points of honor are yours."
	]
	quest.4A82A2B2CD6D0729.quest_subtitle: "Ferment rice into spirit"
	quest.4A82A2B2CD6D0729.quest_desc: [
		"Polished rice, water, and kōji mold left to ferment in cedar — sake is the drink of festival, oath, and offering."
		"Brew it well and the gods, and your lord, will smile upon your table."
		"Brew a bottle of Sake."
	]
	quest.4ACD678A0351D9B2.quest_subtitle: "The altar that holds the offering"
	quest.4ACD678A0351D9B2.quest_desc: [
		"Great rites are not cast from an empty hand. They are laid upon an altar and offered up."
		"Set a Pedestal at the heart of your shrine to hold the implements of the higher arts."
		"Place the Pedestal."
	]
	quest.4B406D180341D483.quest_subtitle: "Yuki-onna, the breath of the white death"
	quest.4B406D180341D483.quest_desc: [
		"She comes down with the blizzard, pale and beautiful, and the breath she gives freezes the marrow in a man."
		"Stand against five yuki-onna upon the snowfields and do not let her smile undo you."
		"Bind the chill of her passing within a fragile soul-gem."
	]
	quest.4B52AFB06B0A7842.quest_subtitle: "Pack rice for the road before you leave"
	quest.4B52AFB06B0A7842.quest_desc: [
		"No inn waits between the provinces, and a starving warrior is a dead one."
		"Roll out sixteen rice balls and stow them in your pack against the long, empty stretches of the highway."
		"Onigiri keep for days and need no fire — the truest provision of the wandering musha."
	]
	quest.4BABE5E39BB9BECB.quest_subtitle: "Hang the skirt of plates that guards the thigh"
	quest.4BABE5E39BB9BECB.quest_desc: [
		"Below the dō hang the kusazuri, the laced skirts of plate that cover the hips and thighs from a low cut."
		"An ashigaru who has stood in the line learns that the killing blow often comes from beneath the shield."
		"Lace on the kusazuri, and close the last gap in your armor."
	]
	quest.4C1ABECB14B6E82C.quest_subtitle: "Lay a bed and survive the first night"
	quest.4C1ABECB14B6E82C.quest_desc: [
		"A weary body is a careless one. Even a wanderer needs a place to lay his head."
		"Set down a bed and sleep until dawn; let the first night pass, and wake to a quieter world."
	]
	quest.4CD369F3FFA38379.quest_subtitle: "Measure your drill against an enemy's"
	quest.4CD369F3FFA38379.quest_desc: [
		"Across the field stands another line, drilled as you were drilled, holding spears as you hold yours."
		"There is no malice in it and no mercy either. The army that breaks first feeds the crows."
		"Defeat twelve enemy ashigaru, and learn that discipline, not hatred, decides the day."
	]
	quest.4CD837DC2E5F700F.quest_subtitle: "Forge the studded iron war-club"
	quest.4CD837DC2E5F700F.quest_desc: [
		"Not all of the smith's craft is edged. The tetsubō is a great iron-bound club, studded and unbreakable."
		"Forge this crushing weapon for those who would shatter armor rather than cut it."
		"An oni's own bar of iron, said to break bone through steel."
	]
	quest.4D6E881748F9D789.quest_subtitle: "Command the exact pace of the works"
	quest.4D6E881748F9D789.quest_desc: [
		"Some works demand a crawl, others a fury; one source cannot serve both."
		"Set a rotation speed controller upon a large cogwheel and dial the rotation to your will."
		"Master the tempo, and every machine obeys your measure."
	]
	quest.4F2D2319D53992F0.quest_subtitle: "Drive back the dark with torchlight"
	quest.4F2D2319D53992F0.quest_desc: [
		"When the sun sets, the realm grows hungry and the dark hides teeth."
		"Bind coal to a stick and make torches. Light is the first wall between you and the night."
	]
	quest.510292BB88FE1B87.quest_subtitle: "The spire that crowns the tower"
	quest.510292BB88FE1B87.quest_desc: [
		"Above the topmost roof rises the sōrin, the bronze spire of rings that gathers heaven to the pagoda's peak."
		"Raise the finished pagoda crown and set the highest piece a temple-builder ever places."
		"Reward: a vermilion pagoda, and two daiku points."
	]
	quest.5199BD332A9CF44F.quest_subtitle: "Sarugami, the wrathful god of the peaks"
	quest.5199BD332A9CF44F.quest_desc: [
		"Older than the shrines, the monkey-god rules the high forests and demands his tribute in blood and in fear."
		"Subdue eight sarugami and break the terror they hold over the mountain folk."
		"From the greatest of them take a soul-gem worthy of a master."
	]
	quest.538FA0C2062E1A75.quest_subtitle: "Pull the thin summer strands"
	quest.538FA0C2062E1A75.quest_desc: [
		"Fine wheat noodles, boiled and chilled, served in clear broth against the summer heat."
		"Sōmen asks patience of the cook and rewards the guest with cool relief."
		"Serve 2 bowls of Sōmen Noodles."
	]
	quest.542978B8D66D5A58.quest_subtitle: "Heap the bowl with rice and topping"
	quest.542978B8D66D5A58.quest_desc: [
		"Donburi — a deep bowl of rice crowned with whatever the kitchen offers, here gilded with mushrooms simmered soft."
		"One bowl, one meal: filling, fast, and dear to every traveler on the road."
		"Cook 2 servings of Mushroom Rice."
	]
	quest.546FEBE112B3F65A.quest_subtitle: "Raise the brewhouse where rice becomes spirit"
	quest.546FEBE112B3F65A.quest_desc: [
		"When the granary overflows, the surplus rice is given to the kura, the brewery."
		"Build the sake brewery, where steamed rice, water, and kōji mould begin their slow change."
		"Reward: a sake barrel, that the brewing may age in the cool dark."
	]
	quest.54EB1E663B4C617C.quest_subtitle: "Lay the grey tile to the ridge"
	quest.54EB1E663B4C617C.quest_desc: [
		"Thatch burns and rots; the kawara tile sheds a typhoon and outlives the carpenter who set it."
		"Fire and stack grey roof tiles enough to clad a hall, course by overlapping course."
		"Reward: roof slabs to finish the eaves."
	]
	quest.563DB9675A65C4B7.quest_subtitle: "The well from which all spells are drawn"
	quest.563DB9675A65C4B7.quest_desc: [
		"Every mantra spends spirit, and the deep caster carries a deeper well."
		"Forge a Ring of Mana and feel your reserve swell beyond the bounds of flesh."
		"Obtain the Ring of Mana."
	]
	quest.56653D704C013A0A.quest_subtitle: "Knap the heads, cut the shafts"
	quest.56653D704C013A0A.quest_desc: [
		"Flint for the head, a straight shaft of wood, a feather for the tail."
		"Fold them together sixty-four times over and fill your quiver against the long night."
		"A bow is hunger; arrows are the bread that feeds it."
	]
	quest.577CB38BAB4FBB9D.quest_subtitle: "The cartridge that feeds the great gun"
	quest.577CB38BAB4FBB9D.quest_desc: [
		"A loose handful of powder burns; a measured charge speaks. The hojutsushi packs each shot into a paper-bound case so the gun roars true every time."
		"Assemble the empty powder charges that will cradle the gunpowder behind the shot."
		"Craft 16 empty powder charges and learn the gunner's measure."
	]
	quest.57A1085CB8C40528.quest_subtitle: "Test your edge against masterless swordsmen"
	quest.57A1085CB8C40528.quest_desc: [
		"The rōnin wander as you do, but lordless and hungry, selling their steel to any who will pay."
		"Among them are swordsmen worthy of the name. Cross blades with twelve and learn what your own journey has made of you."
	]
	quest.586A3BAF8BDDC1D2.quest_subtitle: "Set two wheels to bite as one"
	quest.586A3BAF8BDDC1D2.quest_desc: [
		"A single wheel grinds slow; a matched pair devours."
		"Mount two crushing wheels to turn against each other and feed ore between their teeth."
		"What the millstone whispers, the crushing wheels roar."
	]
	quest.5937797A2F2FD603.quest_subtitle: "Raise a hearth and tame the fire"
	quest.5937797A2F2FD603.quest_desc: [
		"Raw ore and wet clay are useless until the fire has had its way with them."
		"Build a furnace and learn to smelt: ore becomes metal, sand becomes glass, and meat becomes a meal."
	]
	quest.5A836459A6A49EC7.quest_subtitle: "Shape your first humble tools"
	quest.5A836459A6A49EC7.quest_desc: [
		"Wood is soft and the world is hard, yet every master once held a wooden tool."
		"Carve a simple pickaxe. It will not last long, but it will break the first stone for you."
	]
	quest.5BCABB20B5F766DD.quest_subtitle: "Stone awaiting its sigil"
	quest.5BCABB20B5F766DD.quest_desc: [
		"Before the sigil is cut, the talisman is only stone, mute and waiting."
		"Cut blank runestones in number, for a single rite may spend a dozen and leave you wanting."
		"Gather 6 Blank Runestone."
	]
	quest.5C83B1E19AEC1A53.quest_subtitle: "Hold the line against the demon"
	quest.5C83B1E19AEC1A53.quest_desc: [
		"When the oni come down from the hills, swords are not enough. Only a wall of disciplined spears can hold them."
		"The oni-brute fears no single warrior, but it cannot break a line that does not break itself."
		"Slay five oni-brutes, and prove the heihō stronger than the demon's fury."
	]
	quest.5C88635B6EAD3BBA.quest_subtitle: "Fill your stores against the long road"
	quest.5C88635B6EAD3BBA.quest_desc: [
		"No campaign was ever won on an empty belly. Before steel or sutra, a warrior must eat."
		"Bend your back in the paddies and gather the rice that feeds province and army alike."
		"Collect 16 Rice."
	]
	quest.5D378088A5C78E6C.quest_subtitle: "Hitotsume-nyūdō, the one-eyed mountain monk"
	quest.5D378088A5C78E6C.quest_desc: [
		"On the lonely passes a great shaven head turns toward you, and in its brow there burns a single staring eye."
		"Cut down five of the one-eyed priests that haunt the ridgelines."
		"Take the soul that scatters from them into a fragile gem."
	]
	quest.5DA406D1618D7CF4.quest_subtitle: "Fold the steel a thousand times"
	quest.5DA406D1618D7CF4.quest_desc: [
		"Tamahagane is born in the tatara and reborn at the anvil. The smith folds it, beats it, folds it again, driving out the dross with every blow."
		"Refine four ingots of jewel steel. Only from this will a true blade be drawn."
	]
	quest.5DB4D46BB6C42DBD.quest_subtitle: "A charge that bursts among the foe"
	quest.5DB4D46BB6C42DBD.quest_desc: [
		"Pack a hollow shell with powder, seat the fuze, and the gun no longer merely strikes — it detonates within the enemy's ranks."
		"The high-explosive shell scatters fire and iron where it lands, the cruelest fruit of the foundry."
		"Assemble 4 HE shells and rain ruin from the great cannon."
	]
	quest.5E57399F1849A33F.quest_subtitle: "Brew the cha and learn the quiet of the bowl"
	quest.5E57399F1849A33F.quest_desc: [
		"Chanoyu, the way of tea, is harmony, respect, purity, and stillness poured into a single bowl."
		"Brew your gathered leaves into fragrant tea and serve it with a calm hand."
		"In a war-torn realm, the tea room is the one place where no sword is drawn."
	]
	quest.5EEA7607209F634C.quest_subtitle: "Gather the green stone the realm counts as coin"
	quest.5EEA7607209F634C.quest_desc: [
		"In these provinces, wealth is weighed in jade, the green stone the merchants prize."
		"Dig a few shards from the deep rock and feel the realm's currency in your palm."
		"From such small stones, great houses of trade are one day built."
	]
	quest.5F656B28984E0295.quest_subtitle: "Set a curved blade upon a long haft"
	quest.5F656B28984E0295.quest_desc: [
		"The naginata is a sword given the reach of a spear — a curved tamahagane blade lashed to a long shaft."
		"Forge the blade and mount it; it armed the sōhei warrior-monks and the women who guarded the home."
		"With it you sweep a circle of enemies from beyond their reach."
	]
	quest.60CBE8E538C6BB1C.quest_subtitle: "The first true shot"
	quest.60CBE8E538C6BB1C.quest_desc: [
		"Take aim and loose: the simplest act of the way, and the hardest to perfect."
		"Strike a living mark with the bow and feel the line drawn between eye and target."
		"Every kata of kyūjutsu begins from this single, steady breath."
	]
	quest.629B5A44434812CD.quest_subtitle: "Carry the season's leaf to market"
	quest.629B5A44434812CD.quest_desc: [
		"From the misted slopes the tea leaf travels, prized by monk and warlord alike."
		"Bring thirty-two leaves down the tea road and trade them where the chajin gather."
	]
	quest.62F549B8738D3589.quest_subtitle: "Demon-cutting"
	quest.62F549B8738D3589.quest_desc: [
		"When the oni comes down from the mountains, the village prays and the bushi draws. Horned, vast, and merciless, it tests every lesson at once."
		"Fell five oni brutes. Meet the demon's club with your own and prove which iron is harder."
	]
	quest.64679EE0FB4D8755.quest_subtitle: "Minogasa, the rain-cape and woven hat"
	quest.64679EE0FB4D8755.quest_desc: [
		"Before the high passes the yamabushi sheds the silks of the valley and takes up the mino, the straw cape that turns the rain and the cold wind."
		"Weave the straw cape and wear the road upon your shoulders."
		"The mountain receives only those who come to it humble and unadorned."
	]
	quest.647785830C5A632D.quest_subtitle: "Sashimono joinery for the daily room"
	quest.647785830C5A632D.quest_desc: [
		"Sashimono is furniture joined without nails, drawer and door fitted so close no gap admits the dust."
		"Craft cupboards for the living quarters and prove your joints hold in the small as in the great."
		"Reward: a fine table for the hall."
	]
	quest.649E90816322FBD0.quest_subtitle: "Let the squash ripen heavy on the vine"
	quest.649E90816322FBD0.quest_desc: [
		"The kabocha, the winter squash, lies fat among its broad leaves as autumn cools."
		"Gather the hard-skinned gourds; simmered in dashi they sweeten the lean months."
		"What ripens late keeps longest, and the wise farmer plants for the winter to come."
	]
	quest.64AA1D7AE6EE0FB9.quest_subtitle: "Weave a sedge hat against sun and rain"
	quest.64AA1D7AE6EE0FB9.quest_desc: [
		"The kasa shields the pilgrim from the summer glare and the driving rain alike."
		"Take up a woven straw hat — the mark of every traveler who walks the realm on foot."
	]
	quest.65D04C7DB0C4C18D.quest_subtitle: "Bend wind through fire, water, and smoke"
	quest.65D04C7DB0C4C18D.quest_desc: [
		"The fuigo, the bellows of the old smithy, lives again in cased iron."
		"Drive an encased fan and push its breath through flame to blast, through water to wash, through smoke to cure."
		"One wind, many works."
	]
	quest.662F462DAA2C2D54.quest_subtitle: "The ridgepole that carries the hall"
	quest.662F462DAA2C2D54.quest_desc: [
		"Walls hold nothing; it is the hari, the great beam, that bears the weight of the whole roof."
		"Hew framed beams from your seasoned timber and learn how the span is carried across open space."
		"Reward: spare framed beams for the next raising."
	]
	quest.666FD566630BDA2A.quest_subtitle: "Strike a foe from across the field"
	quest.666FD566630BDA2A.quest_desc: [
		"Tōya, the far shot: to fell an enemy who is little more than a speck upon the wind."
		"Drop a distant archer from fifty paces and more, arrow against arrow."
		"When you can kill what you can barely see, the field belongs to your bow."
	]
	quest.67171410B527E3D6.quest_subtitle: "The foundry's first metal"
	quest.67171410B527E3D6.quest_desc: [
		"Bronze served the early guns, but the great cannon hungers for iron. Smelt the ore down and pour it hard and grey."
		"Cast iron is the bones of the foundry, the metal from which barrels, breeches, and shot are wrought."
		"Smelt 16 cast iron ingots and stoke the great foundry to life."
	]
	quest.67EC13CF571C6B40.quest_subtitle: "Cook your first hot meal over the fire"
	quest.67EC13CF571C6B40.quest_desc: [
		"An empty belly wins no battles and walks no roads."
		"Cook meat at your hearth and eat your fill; warm food restores the strength the day has spent."
	]
	quest.69A1C7A7A0EF43A4.quest_subtitle: "Drawers of zelkova heartwood"
	quest.69A1C7A7A0EF43A4.quest_desc: [
		"The keyaki tansu holds a household's cloth and coin behind drawers that glide on a breath."
		"Build chests of zelkova, the prized hardwood of the cabinetmaker, fit for a merchant's storeroom."
		"Reward: keyaki tatami matting, and a daiku point."
	]
	quest.69AFC58953A06A07.quest_subtitle: "Never lose the way again"
	quest.69AFC58953A06A07.quest_desc: [
		"A province at war is a maze of unmarked trails and false turns."
		"Carry a compass, and the four directions will keep their counsel no matter how thick the mist."
		"Obtain a Compass."
	]
	quest.69C87BBBE8659D07.quest_subtitle: "Face the masterless blades at range"
	quest.69C87BBBE8659D07.quest_desc: [
		"The rōnin carries no lord's banner, only a hungry sword and nothing left to lose."
		"Ten of these wave-men will test whether your bow can answer cold steel."
		"Loose before he reaches you; range is the bowman's only mercy."
		"Take up the tengai hat and two points of honor."
	]
	quest.6B2321B7148D4462.quest_subtitle: "The reach of the warrior monk"
	quest.6B2321B7148D4462.quest_desc: [
		"The naginata sweeps where the sword cannot reach, the curved blade upon the long haft favored by the sōhei and the women who guarded the hall."
		"Forge a Tamahagane Naginata and learn to cut the legs from beneath a charging line."
	]
	quest.6DCA0375D3B77D23.quest_subtitle: "Strike sixty bargains across the land"
	quest.6DCA0375D3B77D23.quest_desc: [
		"The ōdana, the great shop, keeps its noren raised from first light to last and turns no customer away."
		"Conclude sixty trades through the villages and your ledgers will outgrow any single town."
	]
	quest.6DE1A30F996C9631.quest_subtitle: "Let the blade fell the tree for you"
	quest.6DE1A30F996C9631.quest_desc: [
		"The nokogiri in a tireless hand cuts where no carpenter stands."
		"Mount a mechanical saw to fell trees, cut logs to planks, and carve stone in a single pass."
		"Set it upon a belt and the lumber comes to you, sawn and stacked."
	]
	quest.6E02038099096C04.quest_subtitle: "The legendary scarlet metal of the gods"
	quest.6E02038099096C04.quest_desc: [
		"Beyond steel lies hihi'irokane, the scarlet metal of legend, soft as ash to the unworthy and harder than oni-bone to the worthy."
		"Obtain the smithing template that unlocks its working. With it a mortal blade may be remade into the stuff of myth."
		"Two points toward the Way of the Sword reward this rite."
	]
	quest.6E48ABB3E4446E66.quest_subtitle: "Fude, the brush that draws the sacred bounds"
	quest.6E48ABB3E4446E66.quest_desc: [
		"No rite is raised without its circle. The ascetic takes up the chalk brush and lays the pentacle stroke by careful stroke."
		"Craft the brush, that your hand may write the figures that bind and ward."
		"A line untrue is a door left open to the dark."
	]
	quest.6EC525B38EE61882.quest_subtitle: "The heartbeat of the bursting shell"
	quest.6EC525B38EE61882.quest_desc: [
		"A solid ball merely strikes; a shell must burst at the right breath. The timed fuze counts the seconds from muzzle to target."
		"Set it too long and the shell digs harmlessly; too short and it bursts in the air."
		"Craft 4 timed fuzes to give your shells their deadly timing."
	]
	quest.6EECFB24AB749E40.quest_subtitle: "Whisk the bowl of green"
	quest.6EECFB24AB749E40.quest_desc: [
		"Chanoyu, the way of tea — leaves grown, dried, and steeped into a quiet ritual older than any war."
		"To pour tea well is to offer peace; even daimyō set down their swords for a single bowl."
		"Brew 2 cups of Tea."
	]
	quest.6FB99640AEA6A4F3.quest_subtitle: "Break the oni that hold the mountain passes"
	quest.6FB99640AEA6A4F3.quest_desc: [
		"Where the road narrows to a barrier-gate in the high passes, the oni gather to bar the way."
		"These brutes are stronger than any man and fear no blade — break eight of them and the passes are yours."
		"Few wanderers face the oni of the barrier and return to speak of it."
	]
	quest.723B7CE73C53DCE9.quest_subtitle: "A servant bound to paper"
	quest.723B7CE73C53DCE9.quest_desc: [
		"The shikigami is the onmyōji's familiar, a spirit folded into a slip of paper and loosed at a word."
		"Inscribe a Conjurer's Talisman, and never again walk to battle alone."
		"Obtain the Conjurer's Talisman."
	]
	quest.73678F164D16CC4B.quest_subtitle: "A barrel that will not burst"
	quest.73678F164D16CC4B.quest_desc: [
		"Cast iron cracks under a heavy charge. Refine it to steel and the barrel holds where lesser metal splits."
		"Each layer is cast, bored, and welded true before it can stand the blast within."
		"Forge 2 steel cannon barrels, the spine of a gun that can be trusted."
	]
	quest.73E645BEF3877292.quest_subtitle: "Forge your first true blade from common iron"
	quest.73E645BEF3877292.quest_desc: [
		"The first metal ōdachi is plain iron — heavy, blunt of grain, and honest."
		"Beat it out at the anvil and grind an edge that bites."
		"It is no masterwork, but it is the first blade you may truly call your own."
	]
	quest.748A2ECECFA9DE9F.quest_subtitle: "Turn rot and straw into the soil's strength"
	quest.748A2ECECFA9DE9F.quest_desc: [
		"A field gives only what it is given. The careful noka returns to the soil what the harvest takes away."
		"Build a composter and let straw, leaves, and scraps rot down into dark, rich earth."
		"Reward: organic compost and bone meal to feed the next year's planting."
	]
	quest.771C11A14F88C13F.quest_subtitle: "Climb to the jagged peaks and endure the cold"
	quest.771C11A14F88C13F.quest_desc: [
		"Above the tree line the air thins and the wind cuts like a drawn blade."
		"Climb to the jagged peaks where the snow never melts, and prove the body can carry the spirit as far as it must go."
	]
	quest.7727BE555EFE5F63.quest_subtitle: "Tengai, the basket that hides the face"
	quest.7727BE555EFE5F63.quest_desc: [
		"The wandering monk weaves a deep basket-hat and lets it swallow his face, that none may know the man beneath the calling."
		"Make the tengai and walk nameless among the villages of the plain."
		"He who has no face cannot be turned aside."
	]
	quest.774D6BD9E65CDB42.quest_subtitle: "A puppet hand that works the recipe"
	quest.774D6BD9E65CDB42.quest_desc: [
		"The kairai, the puppet, mimics the motions of a living hand."
		"Build a deployer to place, use, and craft upon the block before it, tireless and exact."
		"Give it tools and it labors as a karakuri ningyō, the mechanical doll of legend."
	]
	quest.7856CECB8534BB74.quest_subtitle: "Gather the green jade men barter for"
	quest.7856CECB8534BB74.quest_desc: [
		"Steel wins battles, but jade wins the years between them, buying rice, roads, and loyalty alike."
		"Gather a purse of the green stone the realm accepts as coin."
		"Collect 6 Jade."
	]
	quest.7861BC586A1C8127.quest_subtitle: "Turn the new guns on a worthy foe"
	quest.7861BC586A1C8127.quest_desc: [
		"Steel and powder mean nothing until they are proven in fire. The oni brute is armored, furious, and slow to fall — the perfect proving ground."
		"Bring your shells and shot to bear and break 5 of the brutes where they stand."
		"Prove your guns in blood, and the school names you a true master of hojutsu."
	]
	quest.7AB46A101ABC054B.quest_subtitle: "Fold tamahagane into a great blade worthy of the name"
	quest.7AB46A101ABC054B.quest_desc: [
		"Now the swordsmith's art begins in earnest."
		"Fold the tamahagane upon itself, drawing out the slag and layering the grain like flowing water."
		"The tamahagane ōdachi holds an edge no iron blade can match."
	]
	quest.7B3ED8957CA391F4.quest_subtitle: "Seal the grain in urushi lacquer"
	quest.7B3ED8957CA391F4.quest_desc: [
		"Raw timber drinks the rain and rots; lacquered timber endures a hundred winters."
		"Coat sakura wood in urushi until it gleams black-red, the finish of pillars and beams meant to last."
		"Reward: lacquered sakura logs, and a daiku point."
	]
	quest.7B75A9D5E4564614.quest_subtitle: "Close a bargain among the clouds"
	quest.7B75A9D5E4564614.quest_desc: [
		"Where the sky islands drift, a market hangs nearer the heavens than any castle keep."
		"Trade once at the roof of the world and earn the name hoshi-akindo, the star trader of Tenkū."
	]
	quest.7C9856EDF6FE6474.quest_subtitle: "Pluck the first tender leaves from the tea rows"
	quest.7C9856EDF6FE6474.quest_desc: [
		"On the warm hillside the tea bushes grow in long trimmed rows."
		"Pluck only the youngest leaves, two and a bud, in the cool of the morning."
		"Steamed and rolled, these leaves become the drink that steadies monk and warrior alike."
	]
	quest.7D6C01D89D685A99.quest_subtitle: "Bear sixteen flasks of rice wine"
	quest.7D6C01D89D685A99.quest_desc: [
		"No festival nor treaty is sealed without sake, the brewed spirit of the harvest rice."
		"Haul sixteen flasks to the stalls; where the cups are filled, coin flows freely."
	]
	quest.7DD82B003B1563C7.quest_subtitle: "Masterless, but not harmless"
	quest.7DD82B003B1563C7.quest_desc: [
		"The rōnin serves no lord, yet his sword forgot none of its lessons. The roads are thick with them, hungry and quick."
		"Cross ten of them and live. A wandering blade respects only a better one."
	]
	quest.7DE55C5858CDD7C4.quest_subtitle: "Kindle the steelmaker's fire"
	quest.7DE55C5858CDD7C4.quest_desc: [
		"The tatara is the heart of every forge in the land, breathing night and day to wed iron sand and charcoal."
		"Build the furnace whose flame will one day yield tamahagane, the jewel steel of the smiths."
		"Place a Tatara Furnace."
	]
	quest.7F133A8B5ADFF59B.quest_subtitle: "Lattice fitted without a nail"
	quest.7F133A8B5ADFF59B.quest_desc: [
		"Kumiko is the art of slotting thin slats into patterns of light and shadow, each piece shaped to lock the next."
		"Assemble checkered shoji panels and let the lattice do the work of glue and iron alike."
		"Reward: checkered shoji frames for the rooms to come."
	]
	quest.7FDAE1E19453D6F9.quest_subtitle: "Iron enough to break armor and bone"
	quest.7FDAE1E19453D6F9.quest_desc: [
		"The kanabō is no subtle weapon. It is a studded bar of iron, swung to shatter helms and snap the legs of warhorses."
		"Oni are said to carry them; so do the strongest footsoldiers, who need no edge, only weight and wrath."
		"Forge a kanabō, and let the heavy blow do what no point can."
	]
}
